1. Create a folder and the open Anaconda prompt. Then CD to the folder and change drive if necessary (:d). 
    And then open VS code from there, code .
2. Create virtual environment. 
    Open Terminal
    conda create -p venv  python==3.8 -y OR python -m venv env
3. Activate virtual environment
    conda activate venv/ OR .\env\Scripts\activate
4. Synch Github
    git init
    git add . #To commit all the files except .gitignore
    git commit -m "first commit"
    git branch -M main
    git remote add origin https://github.com/manojkumarmr123/Langchain.git
    git push -u origin main
5. Create .gitignore file in github UI and pull through Terminal
    git pull
6. Create requirements.txt and setup.py
    Add "-e ." when you first run the requirements.txt and then comment it for second run onwards
    pip install -r requirements.txt
7. 
    
    
